European Union member countries
should have debt limits written into their constitutions, said
Andreas Schmitz, president of the BdB Association of German
Banks,  Handelsblatt reported .  Governments should be forbidden from having a structural
budget deficit, Schmitz said in an interview, according to the
German newspaper. Schmitz told Handelsblatt he is against joint
